Note:
RUNA SCHEMA - Native Schema/IDL Substrate (Tier 1)

Provides the Runa-native schema declaration substrate. This is the
canonical schema/IDL replacement for JSON Schema, Protobuf, Avro, and
GraphQL SDL per the Universal Substrate Plan.

A Schema describes the shape of a value: its fields, their types,
their constraints, and their documentation. Schemas are first-class
values - a program can construct, inspect, and validate against
schemas at runtime.

TYPE REFS:
  TypeRef is a parametric type reference. Primitive type tags (string,
  integer, float, bool, bytes, datetime, uuid, decimal) cover the
  scalar leaves. Composite type tags (list, map, struct, union,
  reference) cover the structural layer. A struct TypeRef points at
  another Schema by name (resolved via a schema registry the caller
  maintains).

CONSTRAINTS:
  TypeConstraint is a tagged ADT capturing the validation rules
  defined by JSON Schema Draft 2020-12 and the Protobuf field options:
  MinValue, MaxValue, MinLength, MaxLength, Pattern (regex source),
  Enum (allowed values), OneOf (union member), AllOf (intersection),
  NotNull, Unique (collection), Range (numeric).

Layout (Schema, 56 bytes):
  offset  0 : name         (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : namespace    (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 16 : version      (8 bytes, Version pointer or 0)
  offset 24 : fields       (8 bytes, List<FieldSpec> pointer)
  offset 32 : constraints  (8 bytes, List<ValidationRule> pointer - cross-field invariants)
  offset 40 : documentation (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 48 : kind         (8 bytes, see SCHEMA_KIND_*)

Layout (FieldSpec, 56 bytes):
  offset  0 : name         (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : type_ref     (8 bytes, TypeRef pointer)
  offset 16 : nullable     (8 bytes, 0 = required non-null, 1 = nullable)
  offset 24 : default      (8 bytes, ConfigValue pointer or 0)
  offset 32 : constraints  (8 bytes, List<TypeConstraint> pointer or 0)
  offset 40 : documentation (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 48 : json_field   (8 bytes, String pointer or 0 - JSON wire name override)

Layout (TypeRef, 32 bytes):
  offset  0 : primitive    (8 bytes, see TYPE_* constants; 0 if composite)
  offset  8 : composite    (8 bytes, see COMP_* constants; 0 if primitive)
  offset 16 : inner1       (8 bytes, child TypeRef for list/map values)
  offset 24 : inner2       (8 bytes, child TypeRef for map keys; Schema-name String for COMP_REF)

Layout (TypeConstraint, 40 bytes):
  offset  0 : kind         (8 bytes, see CONSTRAINT_* constants)
  offset  8 : numeric_arg  (8 bytes, for Min/Max/Range/Length bounds)
  offset 16 : numeric_arg2  (8 bytes, second bound for Range)
  offset 24 : string_arg    (8 bytes, regex source or enum-value list pointer)
  offset 32 : ref_arg       (8 bytes, OneOf/AllOf TypeRef pointer)

Layout (ValidationRule, 24 bytes):
  offset  0 : field_path   (8 bytes, String pointer - dotted field path)
  offset  8 : constraint   (8 bytes, TypeConstraint pointer)
  offset 16 : message      (8 bytes, String pointer or 0 - human description)

References:
  - JSON Schema Draft 2020-12  https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema
  - Protocol Buffers Language  https://protobuf.dev/programming-guides/proto3/
  - Apache Avro Specification  https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.11.1/specification/
  - GraphQL SDL                https://spec.graphql.org/October2021/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/config.runa" as Cfg

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let SCHEMA_SIZE be 56
Let FIELD_SPEC_SIZE be 56
Let TYPE_REF_SIZE be 32
Let TYPE_CONSTRAINT_SIZE be 40
Let VALIDATION_RULE_SIZE be 24

Let SCHEMA_KIND_RECORD be 1
Let SCHEMA_KIND_ENUM be 2
Let SCHEMA_KIND_UNION be 3
Let SCHEMA_KIND_INTERFACE be 4

Note: Primitive type tags.
Let TYPE_STRING be 1
Let TYPE_INTEGER be 2
Let TYPE_FLOAT be 3
Let TYPE_BOOL be 4
Let TYPE_BYTES be 5
Let TYPE_DATETIME be 6
Let TYPE_UUID be 7
Let TYPE_DECIMAL be 8
Let TYPE_NULL be 9

Note: Composite type tags.
Let COMP_LIST be 1
Let COMP_MAP be 2
Let COMP_REF be 3
Let COMP_UNION be 4

Note: Constraint kinds.
Let CONSTRAINT_MIN_VALUE be 1
Let CONSTRAINT_MAX_VALUE be 2
Let CONSTRAINT_MIN_LENGTH be 3
Let CONSTRAINT_MAX_LENGTH be 4
Let CONSTRAINT_PATTERN be 5
Let CONSTRAINT_ENUM be 6
Let CONSTRAINT_ONE_OF be 7
Let CONSTRAINT_ALL_OF be 8
Let CONSTRAINT_NOT_NULL be 9
Let CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE be 10
Let CONSTRAINT_RANGE be 11

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE REFERENCES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a primitive TypeRef. Used to declare scalar field types.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes, store the primitive tag, zero everything else.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on out-of-range tag.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_primitive" takes primitive_tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If primitive_tag is less than TYPE_STRING:
        Return 0
    End If
    If primitive_tag is greater than TYPE_NULL:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let t be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_REF_SIZE
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 0, primitive_tag
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 24, 0
    Return t
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a list TypeRef parametrized by an element TypeRef. The
element TypeRef is adopted; the parent disposes it on destroy_deep.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes, store COMP_LIST and the element TypeRef pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null element.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_list" takes element as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let t be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_REF_SIZE
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 8, COMP_LIST
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 16, element
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 24, 0
    Return t
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a map TypeRef parametrized by key TypeRef and value TypeRef.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate, store COMP_MAP, value at inner1, key at inner2.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on either null operand.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_map" takes key_type as Integer, value_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If key_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let t be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_REF_SIZE
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 8, COMP_MAP
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 16, value_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 24, key_type
    Return t
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a reference TypeRef pointing at another Schema by name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate, store COMP_REF, duplicate the name into inner2.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null name.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_named" takes schema_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with schema_name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let t be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_REF_SIZE
    If t is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 8, COMP_REF
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 24, name_copy
    Return t
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a TypeRef and recursively free its inner refs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
For composite refs, recurse into inner1/inner2. COMP_REF's inner2 is a
String pointer; free it. Then free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(d) tree depth. Space: O(d) recursion.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_destroy" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let comp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 8
    If comp is equal to COMP_LIST:
        Let inner be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 16
        If inner is not equal to 0:
            proc type_ref_destroy with inner
        End If
    End If
    If comp is equal to COMP_MAP:
        Let val_ref be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 16
        If val_ref is not equal to 0:
            proc type_ref_destroy with val_ref
        End If
        Let key_ref be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 24
        If key_ref is not equal to 0:
            proc type_ref_destroy with key_ref
        End If
    End If
    If comp is equal to COMP_REF:
        Let name_str be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 24
        If name_str is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with name_str
        End If
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with t
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
True if the TypeRef is a primitive type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Check whether the primitive slot is non-zero.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_is_primitive" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 0
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the primitive tag (or 0 if composite).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_primitive_tag" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the composite tag (or 0 if primitive).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "type_ref_composite_tag" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE CONSTRAINTS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a numeric-bound constraint (MinValue, MaxValue, MinLength,
MaxLength).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 40 bytes, store kind and the numeric bound.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on out-of-range kind.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_numeric" takes kind as Integer, bound as Integer returns Integer:
    If kind is less than CONSTRAINT_MIN_VALUE:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kind is greater than CONSTRAINT_MAX_LENGTH:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_CONSTRAINT_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, bound
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, 0
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a Range constraint with inclusive low / high bounds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 40 bytes, store CONSTRAINT_RANGE, low at numeric_arg, high at
numeric_arg2.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller is responsible for low <= high.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_range" takes low as Integer, high as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_CONSTRAINT_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, CONSTRAINT_RANGE
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, low
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, high
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, 0
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a Pattern constraint with a regex source string. The string
is duplicated so the constraint owns it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 40 bytes, store CONSTRAINT_PATTERN, duplicate the regex.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|pattern|). Space: O(|pattern|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null pattern. The regex itself is not validated here;
validation happens when the pattern is applied via the regex engine.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_pattern" takes regex_source as Integer returns Integer:
    If regex_source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pattern_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with regex_source
    If pattern_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_CONSTRAINT_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with pattern_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, CONSTRAINT_PATTERN
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, pattern_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, 0
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a NotNull constraint.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate, store kind, zero the rest.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_not_null" returns Integer:
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_CONSTRAINT_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, CONSTRAINT_NOT_NULL
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, 0
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a Unique constraint (for list / set fields).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate, store kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_unique" returns Integer:
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with TYPE_CONSTRAINT_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, 0
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a TypeConstraint and any owned subordinate (the pattern string).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the string_arg if non-null, then the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_destroy" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 0
    If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_PATTERN:
        Let s be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 24
        If s is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with s
        End If
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the constraint kind discriminator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_kind" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the numeric bound for Min*/Max* constraints; 0 for others.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_numeric_arg" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: FIELD SPEC
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a FieldSpec with name and type. Default value, constraints,
documentation, and JSON wire name are set via dedicated setters.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate the name, allocate 56 bytes, populate name + type_ref,
default nullable to 0 (required non-null), zero the rest.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null name or type.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_create" takes name as Integer, type_ref as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type_ref is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let constraints be proc list_create from List
    If constraints is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let f be proc allocate from Layout with FIELD_SPEC_SIZE
    If f is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with constraints
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 0, name_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 8, type_ref
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 32, constraints
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 48, 0
    Return f
End Process

@Reasoning
Mark a field as nullable (allows the value to be missing or null).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Set the nullable flag.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_set_nullable" takes f as Integer, nullable as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be 0
    If nullable is equal to 1:
        Set n to 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 16, n
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Attach a constraint to the field.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Push the constraint pointer onto the field's constraints list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The field adopts the constraint pointer; release via field_spec_destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_add_constraint" takes f as Integer, c as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 32
    If constraints is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc list_push from List with constraints, c
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Set the field's default value (a ConfigValue from the config module).
The field adopts the pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free any existing default, then store the new pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(d) for the prior cleanup. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller transfers ownership.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_set_default" takes f as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let prior be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
    If prior is not equal to 0:
        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with prior
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with f, 24, default_value
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the field name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_name" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the field type reference.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_type" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
True if the field is nullable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_is_nullable" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the constraint list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_constraints" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Free a FieldSpec and all owned subordinates.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free name, default, every constraint in the list, type_ref, then the
record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(c) for the constraint count. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "field_spec_destroy" takes f as Integer returns Integer:
    If f is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let type_ref be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 8
    If type_ref is not equal to 0:
        proc type_ref_destroy with type_ref
    End If
    Let default_v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 24
    If default_v is not equal to 0:
        proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with default_v
    End If
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 32
    If constraints is not equal to 0:
        Let cn be proc list_length from List with constraints
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than cn:
            Let c be proc list_get from List with constraints, i
            If c is not equal to 0:
                proc constraint_destroy with c
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with constraints
    End If
    Let docs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 40
    If docs is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with docs
    End If
    Let jf be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with f, 48
    If jf is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with jf
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with f
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SCHEMA
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct an empty Schema with the given name and kind.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 56 bytes, duplicate the name, create the empty fields and
constraints lists, populate kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null name or out-of-range kind.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create_named" takes name as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kind is less than SCHEMA_KIND_RECORD:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kind is greater than SCHEMA_KIND_INTERFACE:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let fields be proc list_create from List
    If fields is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let constraints be proc list_create from List
    If constraints is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with fields
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let s be proc allocate from Layout with SCHEMA_SIZE
    If s is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with constraints
        proc list_destroy from List with fields
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 0, name_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 24, fields
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 32, constraints
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 48, kind
    Return s
End Process

@Reasoning
Append a field declaration to the schema.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Push the FieldSpec onto the fields list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The schema adopts the FieldSpec.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_add_field" takes s as Integer, field as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If field is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 24
    If fields is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc list_push from List with fields, field
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the schema and all owned fields.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterate fields calling field_spec_destroy; destroy the list headers;
free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(f) for f fields. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_destroy_named" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let ns be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
    If ns is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with ns
    End If
    Let fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 24
    If fields is not equal to 0:
        Let fn be proc list_length from List with fields
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than fn:
            Let f be proc list_get from List with fields, i
            If f is not equal to 0:
                proc field_spec_destroy with f
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with fields
    End If
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 32
    If constraints is not equal to 0:
        Let cn be proc list_length from List with constraints
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than cn:
            Let cc be proc list_get from List with constraints, j
            If cc is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with cc
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with constraints
    End If
    Let docs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 40
    If docs is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with docs
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with s
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the schema name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_name" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the schema's field list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_fields" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Find a field by name. Linear scan; schemas typically have well-bounded
field counts.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterate the fields list comparing names with string_equals.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(f * |name|). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if no field of the given name exists.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_find_field" takes s as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 24
    If fields is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with fields
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let f be proc list_get from List with fields, i
        If f is not equal to 0:
            Let fn be proc field_spec_name with f
            If fn is not equal to 0:
                Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with fn, name
                If eq is equal to 1:
                    Return f
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VALIDATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Validate a ConfigValue against a single TypeConstraint. Returns 1 if
the constraint is satisfied, 0 otherwise. Used as the inner loop of
schema_validate.

Constraints implemented in this module:
  CONSTRAINT_MIN_VALUE / MAX_VALUE / RANGE   for CV_INTEGER
  CONSTRAINT_MIN_LENGTH / MAX_LENGTH         for CV_STRING and CV_LIST
  CONSTRAINT_NOT_NULL                        for any kind
  CONSTRAINT_UNIQUE                          for CV_LIST (O(n^2) check)

CONSTRAINT_PATTERN, CONSTRAINT_ENUM, CONSTRAINT_ONE_OF, and
CONSTRAINT_ALL_OF require a regex engine and union resolver that live
in higher-tier modules. This module returns 1 (pass-through) for those
kinds so the validator does not falsely reject; callers that need
full coverage drive those constraints through the schema-specific
validators in json_schema.runa et al.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on constraint kind. For each implemented constraint, dispatch
to a private check helper that interrogates the ConfigValue kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) for scalar constraints, O(n) for length checks, O(n^2) for
Unique. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Constraint failures are reported via return value; callers escalate.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "check_constraint" takes value as Integer, c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 0
    If value is equal to 0:
        If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_NOT_NULL:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    Let vkind be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
    If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_NOT_NULL:
        If vkind is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_MIN_VALUE:
        If vkind is equal to 2:
            Let iv be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with value
            Let bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
            If iv is less than bound:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_MAX_VALUE:
        If vkind is equal to 2:
            Let iv2 be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with value
            Let bound2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
            If iv2 is greater than bound2:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_RANGE:
        If vkind is equal to 2:
            Let iv3 be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with value
            Let low be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
            Let high be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 16
            If iv3 is less than low:
                Return 0
            End If
            If iv3 is greater than high:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_MIN_LENGTH:
        Let mn_bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
        If vkind is equal to 1:
            Let s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with value
            If s is not equal to 0:
                Let sl be proc string_length from StringCore with s
                If sl is less than mn_bound:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If vkind is equal to 5:
            Let lst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with value
            If lst is not equal to 0:
                Let ll be proc list_length from List with lst
                If ll is less than mn_bound:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to CONSTRAINT_MAX_LENGTH:
        Let mx_bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
        If vkind is equal to 1:
            Let ss be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with value
            If ss is not equal to 0:
                Let ssl be proc string_length from StringCore with ss
                If ssl is greater than mx_bound:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If vkind is equal to 5:
            Let lst2 be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with value
            If lst2 is not equal to 0:
                Let ll2 be proc list_length from List with lst2
                If ll2 is greater than mx_bound:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Validate a ConfigValue against a Schema. Returns the number of
constraint violations. Zero means valid.

Behavior:
  - For each declared field, look up the corresponding value in the
    input. If absent and not nullable, count one violation.
  - If present, validate each attached constraint via check_constraint.
  - Cross-field invariants (offset 32 constraints list) are evaluated
    after per-field passes; callers wire those via custom validators.

The input value is expected to be a CV_MAP. Non-map inputs against
SCHEMA_KIND_RECORD count one violation (type mismatch at top level).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the field list. For each field, fetch the value via
get_field_value (top-level Dict lookup). Run NOT_NULL plus
field-level constraint checks. Sum the violation count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(f * c) where f is field count and c is average constraint
count. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Validation is the gating step before schema-bound values are accepted
into application logic; failure must escalate to a caller-supplied
error path.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_validate_value" takes s as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 48
    If kind is equal to SCHEMA_KIND_RECORD:
        If value is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Let vkind be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
        If vkind is not equal to 6:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let violations be 0
    Let fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 24
    If fields is equal to 0:
        Return violations
    End If
    Let map_dict be 0
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Set map_dict to proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with value
    End If

    Let count be proc list_length from List with fields
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let field be proc list_get from List with fields, i
        If field is not equal to 0:
            Let field_name be proc field_spec_name with field
            Let field_value be 0
            If map_dict is not equal to 0:
                If field_name is not equal to 0:
                    Set field_value to proc get from Dict with map_dict, field_name
                End If
            End If
            If field_value is equal to 0:
                Let nullable be proc field_spec_is_nullable with field
                If nullable is equal to 0:
                    Set violations to violations plus 1
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Let constraints be proc field_spec_constraints with field
                If constraints is not equal to 0:
                    Let cn be proc list_length from List with constraints
                    Let j be 0
                    While j is less than cn:
                        Let con be proc list_get from List with constraints, j
                        If con is not equal to 0:
                            Let ok be proc check_constraint with field_value, con
                            If ok is equal to 0:
                                Set violations to violations plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set j to j plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return violations
End Process
